claim.claim-text:
1. A method of producing a laminated ceramic electronic component comprising the steps of: 
printing ceramic paste on a carrier film except in a portion where an internal electrode is to be provided and the vicinity thereof; 
printing internal electrode paste on the carrier film in the portion where an internal electrode is to be provided to define a green sheet including a ceramic paste layer and an internal electrode paste layer, both of which are provided with a space therebetween; 
repeatedly press bonding a laminate including the green sheet and the carrier film to another green sheet on a lamination stage and separating the carrier film to laminate the green sheets and to obtain a ceramic laminate; and 
firing the ceramic laminate to obtain a ceramic sintered body.

7. A method of producing a laminated ceramic electronic component comprising the steps of: 
preparing first and second composite sheets each of which is supported on a carrier film, and each of which includes an internal electrode paste layer and a ceramic green sheet layer, which are provided with a space therebetween such that the internal paste layer passes through the ceramic green sheet from one of both main surfaces to the other; 
press-bonding the first composite sheet to another green sheet on a lamination stage, and then separating the carrier film; 
laminating the second composite sheet on the first composite sheet, press-bonding both sheets, and then separating the carrier film of the second composite sheet to form an internal electrode including a laminate of the internal electrode paste layers of the first and second composite sheets; and 
sintering the laminate obtained in the lamination step to obtain a ceramic sintered body.

8. A method of producing a laminated ceramic electronic component comprising the steps of: 
forming an electrode green sheet which is supported by a carrier film, and which includes an internal inductance electrode configured to pass through a ceramic layer from the upper surface to the lower surface thereof, and a ceramic layer provided around the internal electrode with a space provided therebetween; 
forming a connecting electrode green sheet which is supported by a carrier film, and which includes a connecting electrode formed to be exposed from the upper surface to the lower surface thereof, and a ceramic layer formed around the connecting electrode with a space therebetween; 
laminating a plurality of the electrode green sheets and the connecting electrode green sheets while separating the carrier films such that the internal inductance electrodes are electrically connected through the connecting electrodes to define a coil and to obtain a laminate; and 
firing the laminate to obtain a ceramic sintered body.

14. A method of producing a laminated ceramic electronic component comprising the steps of: 
preparing a composite green sheet which is supported on a carrier film, and which includes an internal electrode paste layer configured to pass through a ceramic green sheet from one of two main surfaces to the other of two main surfaces and the ceramic green sheet layer provided around the internal electrode paste layer with a space provided therebetween; 
forming a void forming green sheet which is supported on a carrier film and which includes a void forming material layer that is capable of being burned down during firing and configured to pass through a ceramic green sheet from one of both main surface to the other thereof and to overlap the internal electrode paste layer of the composite sheet when laminated thereon, and the ceramic green sheet formed around the void forming material layer; 
press-bonding the composite green sheet to another green sheet on a lamination stage and then separating the carrier film; 
laminating the void forming green sheet on the composite green sheet, press-bonding both green sheets and then separating the carrier film to laminate the void forming material layer on the internal electrode paste layer; and 
repeating the lamination step, laminating unpatterned ceramic green sheets on the upper and lower surfaces of the resultant laminate, and then firing the laminate to burn down the void forming material layers to obtain a ceramic sintered body in which a void is formed in at least one of the upper and lower surfaces of an internal electrode.

16. A method of producing a laminated ceramic electronic component comprising the steps of: 
preparing a composite green sheet which is supported on a carrier film, and which includes an internal inductance electrode configured to pass through a ceramic green sheet from the upper surface to the lower surface thereof, and the ceramic green sheet layer provided around the internal inductance electrode with a space provided therebetween; 
forming a connecting electrode green sheet which is supported on a carrier film and which includes a void forming material layer composed of a material that is capable of burning down during firing and provided to overlap the internal inductance electrode of the composite sheet when laminated thereon and pass through the connecting electrode green sheet from the upper surface to the lower surface thereof, a connecting electrode provided at one end of the void forming material layer to be exposed from the upper and lower surfaces, and a ceramic green sheet layer provided around the void forming material layer and the connecting electrode; 
laminating a plurality of the composite green sheets and the connecting electrode green sheets such that the internal inductance electrodes are electrically connected through the connecting electrodes, and the void forming material layer overlaps at least one of the upper and lower surfaces of each of the internal electrodes for inductance, and further laminating unpatterned green sheets on the upper and lower surfaces of the laminate; 
firing the laminate to obtain a ceramic sintered body in which a void is provided in contact with at least one of the upper and lower surfaces of the internal electrodes for inductance.
